Apple's San Francisco is the default system font for React Native on iOS. Apple also offers a rounded version called SF Pro Rounded, used in apps like Reminders. While Swift apps can utilize this font variant by setting the [Font.Design](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/font/design) to `rounded`, I couldn't find any information on how to implement it in React Native, prompting me to create this post.

## How to use SF Pro Rounded with React Native

React Native supports the `ui-rounded` font family by default. You can use it in your app by setting the `fontFamily` prop to `ui-rounded`. Learn more about `ui-rounded` [here](https://drafts.csswg.org/css-fonts-4/#ui-rounded-def).

```tsx
import { Text, StyleSheet } from "react-native";

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  text: {
    fontFamily: "ui-rounded",
  },
});
```

## SF Pro Rounded with NativeWind

Extend your NativeWind theme to include the `ui-rounded` font family.

```ts
import { extendTheme } from "nativewind";

module.exports = {
  content: ["./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}"],
  presets: [require("nativewind/preset")],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      fontFamily: {
        rounded: ["ui-rounded", "system-ui", "sans-serif"],
      },
    },
  },
};
```

Then use it in your app:

```tsx
import { View, Text, StyleSheet } from "react-native";

function App() {
  return (
    <View>
      <Text className="font-rounded">Hello, world!</Text>
    </View>
  );
}
```

## Setting a global font family in React Native

In React Native, styles do not cascade like in regular CSS. One way to set a global font family is to create a custom `<Text />` component that applies the font family throughout the app.

```tsx
import { Text as RNText, StyleSheet } from "react-native";
import cn from "clsx";

function Text({ children, className, ...props }: TextProps) {
  return (
    <RNText className={cn("font-rounded", className)} {...props}>
      {children}
    </RNText>
  );
}
```

## Other variants: SF Mono

React Native also supports the `ui-monospace` font family [out of the box](https://reactnative.dev/docs/text-style-props#fontfamily). You can use it in your iOS app by setting the `fontFamily` prop to `ui-monospace`.
